# Nox macOS app & adapters

Applies to shipping target `Nox/` and future `Apps/NoxMac/`. This layer **implements** `NoxPlatformContracts`; it may import shared packages + all macOS frameworks required.

## Belongs here (not in shared Core)

- **Lifecycle**: `Nox/App/*` (`AppEnvironment`, `NoxContextService`, `NoxAppRuntime`, delegate).
- **Observation**: `NoxActivityObserver`, `NoxAXFocusMonitor`, `NoxWindowContextReader`.
- **Permissions**: `NoxPermissionService`.
- **System**: `NoxSystemStateProvider`, `NoxSystemActionExecutor`, `NoxCaffeinateController`.
- **Calendar / notifications**: `NoxCalendarContextProvider`, `NoxAmbientNotificationEngine`.
- **Persistence**: all `*Store.swift`, `SQLite3`, `NoxPersistencePaths`, `NoxSQLiteBindings`.
- **Presence mesh**: `LocalHTTPPresenceTransport`, Bonjour/BT discovery, `PresenceMeshManager`, keychain identity.
- **UI**: `Nox/Features/**`, SwiftUI/AppKit design system (`NoxDesignTokens`, materials, menu bar, windowing).

## Composition rules

- Wire contracts in one place (today `NoxContextService`); do not let `Packages/*` reference `AppEnvironment` or `NSStatusItem`.
- New mac-only features: add protocol to `NoxPlatformContracts` if other platforms will need a stub later; implement in adapter.
- Do not move `NoxContextService` wholesale into Core — split orchestration vs mac wiring only in Phase 4.

## UI copy

- Follow `Docs/NOX_UI_COPY_RULES.md`: observational, not engine/telemetry voice.

## When adding iOS/iPadOS/etc. later

- New app target under `Apps/`; **reuse packages + contracts**; provide platform adapters only.
- Never port desktop observation or canonical SQLite ownership to phone/tablet without sync design.
